Day 1 of My Linux Journey->> 

->Linux is an open-source operating system, basically the layer that sits between you (the user) and your hardware (like CPU, RAM, disk, etc.).

->It makes sure apps donâ€™t fight for resources, keeps everything organized, and protects your system from crashing or leaking data. 

Why Linux though?

 ->Free & Open Source â€“ No license headaches, and you can see everything under the hood.
->Lightweight & Fast â€“ Doesnâ€™t hog resources like some other OSes.
