->DevOps Friendly â€“ Most cloud-native tools are made to run on Linux. Highly -->Customizable â€“ From the UI to the internals, you can tweak it all.

How is Linux actually structured? 

+----------------------------------------------------+
| User Applications (Vim, Docker, Apache, etc.)   |
+----------------------------------------------------+
| Shell (Bash, Zsh, Fish, etc.)          | <-- Part of the OS
+----------------------------------------------------+
| System Libraries (glibc, libc, OpenSSL, etc.)  | <-- Part of the OS
+----------------------------------------------------+
| System Utilities (ls, grep, systemctl, etc.)   | <-- Part of the OS
+----------------------------------------------------+
| Linux Kernel (Processes, Memory, FS, Network)    | <-- Core of the OS
+----------------------------------------------------+
| Hardware (CPU, RAM, Disk, Network, Peripherals)  |
+----------------------------------------------------+

